<subSubSection box="[425,890,1205,1231]" pageId="23" pageNumber="1103" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="23.[425,890,1205,1231]" box="[425,890,1205,1231]" pageId="23" pageNumber="1103">
(
<figureCitation box="[433,537,1205,1231]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="5.[160,225,1145,1168]" captionTargetBox="[194,1153,143,1113]" captionTargetId="figure-187@5.[163,1153,142,1113]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 1. Dorsal habitus. (a) S Scatonomus barbatus stat. rev.; (b) S. canhedoae sp. nov.; (holotype); (c) S. chalybaeus; (d) S. fasciculatus; (e) S. foresti sp. nov. (holotype); (f) S. insignis; (g) S. janssensi; (h) S. mitzae sp. nov. (holotype); (i) S. paulosawayai (holotype); (j, k) S. thalassinus; (l) S. viridis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5020905" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5020905/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="1103">Figures 1</figureCitation>
(h), 3(h), 4(a, d), 5(g) and 6(a))
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="1103" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="23.[160,1156,1307,1436]" box="[160,285,1307,1331]" pageId="23" pageNumber="1103">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,285,1307,1331]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="1103">Etymology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[160,1156,1307,1436]" pageId="23" pageNumber="1103">Named in honour of Mileva ‘Mitza’ Meric Einstein. Mileva was a talented Serbian physicist. She was Albert Einstein’s first wife, and her contributions to his groundbreaking science are hotly discussed.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="1103" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="23.[160,1156,1495,1728]" box="[160,276,1495,1519]" pageId="23" pageNumber="1103">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,276,1495,1519]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="1103">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[160,1156,1495,1728]" pageId="23" pageNumber="1103">
<taxonomicName authority="Valois &amp; Vaz-de-Mello &amp; Silva, 2020" authorityName="Valois &amp; Vaz-de-Mello &amp; Silva" authorityYear="2020" box="[160,374,1530,1555]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Scatonomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="1103" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mitzae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[160,374,1530,1555]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="1103">Scatonomus mitzae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[381,468,1530,1555]" pageId="23" pageNumber="1103" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
seems to be closely related to 
<taxonomicName authority="viridis" authorityName="viridis Erichson" authorityYear="1835" box="[818,976,1530,1555]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Scatonomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="1103" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="viridis" subSpecies="viridis">
<emphasis box="[818,976,1530,1555]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="1103">S. viridis viridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pereira" authorityYear="1954" box="[1033,1155,1530,1555]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Scatonomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="1103" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="janssensi">
<emphasis box="[1033,1155,1530,1555]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="1103">S. janssensi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having a single central emargination on clypeal edge, without teeth or lateral emarginations (
<figureCitation box="[257,349,1599,1624]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="7.[160,225,1294,1317]" captionTargetBox="[171,1141,146,1237]" captionTargetId="figure-89@7.[163,1153,142,1262]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 3. Head, dorsal view. (a) Scatonomus barbatus stat. rev.; (b) S. canhedoae sp. nov. (holotype); (c) S. chalybaeus; (d) S. fasciculatus; (e) S. foresti sp. nov. (holotype); (f) S. insignis; (g) S. janssensi; (h) S. mitzae sp. nov. (holotype); (i) S. paulosawayai (holotype); (j, k) S. thalassinus; (l) S. viridis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5020909" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5020909/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="1103">Figure 3</figureCitation>
(g, h, l)). However, 
<taxonomicName authority="Valois &amp; Vaz-de-Mello &amp; Silva, 2020" authorityName="Valois &amp; Vaz-de-Mello &amp; Silva" authorityYear="2020" box="[554,651,1599,1624]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Scatonomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="1103" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mitzae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[554,651,1599,1624]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="1103">S. mitzae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[658,744,1599,1624]" pageId="23" pageNumber="1103" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is distinguished by having a deep Ushaped clypeal emargination (
<figureCitation box="[498,590,1634,1659]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="7.[160,225,1294,1317]" captionTargetBox="[171,1141,146,1237]" captionTargetId="figure-89@7.[163,1153,142,1262]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 3. Head, dorsal view. (a) Scatonomus barbatus stat. rev.; (b) S. canhedoae sp. nov. (holotype); (c) S. chalybaeus; (d) S. fasciculatus; (e) S. foresti sp. nov. (holotype); (f) S. insignis; (g) S. janssensi; (h) S. mitzae sp. nov. (holotype); (i) S. paulosawayai (holotype); (j, k) S. thalassinus; (l) S. viridis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5020909" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5020909/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="1103">Figure 3</figureCitation>
(h)). Antennal club densely coated with long setae. Elytral striae thin (
<figureCitation box="[368,462,1669,1694]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="8.[160,225,904,927]" captionTargetBox="[166,1143,144,862]" captionTargetId="figure-495@8.[163,1153,142,873]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figure 4. Details of Scatonomus morphology. (a) S. mitzae sp. nov., microgranulated interstrial surface (white arrow indicating the elytral stria); (b) S. janssensi, detail of elytral striae; (c) S. thalassinus, surface of pronotal disc (wrinkles, square); (d) S. mitzae sp. nov., puncticulate pronotal surface (white arrow, a coase puncture; black arrow, a fine puncture); (e) S. janssensi, ocellate punctures on pronotum; (f) S. fasciculatus, striate surface on mesepimeron; (g) S. janssensi, broad and transverse carina at the posterior portion of clypeus (white arrow) and longitudinal carina (black arrow); (h) holotype of S. xanthopygus (synonym of S. chalybaeus), dry body fat partially covering the pygidial disc; (i, j) Abdominal ventrites of S. thalassinus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5020911" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5020911/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="1103">Figure 4</figureCitation>
(a), arrow); width of striae on disc at least 10 times narrower than the third interstria.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="1104" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="24.[160,1156,143,1173]" box="[160,294,143,167]" pageId="24" pageNumber="1104">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,294,143,167]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="1104">Description</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[160,1156,143,1173]" pageId="24" pageNumber="1104">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,218,178,203]" pageId="24" pageNumber="1104">Male</emphasis>
: Length: 15.0– 
<quantity box="[381,483,178,203]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.54" pageId="24" pageNumber="1104" unit="mm" value="15.4">15.4 mm</quantity>
. Body black, with greenish or yellowish reflections (
<figureCitation box="[1063,1155,178,203]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="5.[160,225,1145,1168]" captionTargetBox="[194,1153,143,1113]" captionTargetId="figure-187@5.[163,1153,142,1113]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 1. Dorsal habitus. (a) S Scatonomus barbatus stat. rev.; (b) S. canhedoae sp. nov.; (holotype); (c) S. chalybaeus; (d) S. fasciculatus; (e) S. foresti sp. nov. (holotype); (f) S. insignis; (g) S. janssensi; (h) S. mitzae sp. nov. (holotype); (i) S. paulosawayai (holotype); (j, k) S. thalassinus; (l) S. viridis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5020905" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5020905/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="1104">Figure 1</figureCitation>
(h)). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[211,273,212,237]" pageId="24" pageNumber="1104">Head</emphasis>
: surface wrinkled and densely punctate (
<figureCitation box="[740,835,212,237]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="7.[160,225,1294,1317]" captionTargetBox="[171,1141,146,1237]" captionTargetId="figure-89@7.[163,1153,142,1262]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 3. Head, dorsal view. (a) Scatonomus barbatus stat. rev.; (b) S. canhedoae sp. nov. (holotype); (c) S. chalybaeus; (d) S. fasciculatus; (e) S. foresti sp. nov. (holotype); (f) S. insignis; (g) S. janssensi; (h) S. mitzae sp. nov. (holotype); (i) S. paulosawayai (holotype); (j, k) S. thalassinus; (l) S. viridis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5020909" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5020909/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="1104">Figure 3</figureCitation>
(h)). Posterior edge narrowly margined medially (
<figureCitation box="[394,491,247,272]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="7.[160,225,1294,1317]" captionTargetBox="[171,1141,146,1237]" captionTargetId="figure-89@7.[163,1153,142,1262]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 3. Head, dorsal view. (a) Scatonomus barbatus stat. rev.; (b) S. canhedoae sp. nov. (holotype); (c) S. chalybaeus; (d) S. fasciculatus; (e) S. foresti sp. nov. (holotype); (f) S. insignis; (g) S. janssensi; (h) S. mitzae sp. nov. (holotype); (i) S. paulosawayai (holotype); (j, k) S. thalassinus; (l) S. viridis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5020909" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5020909/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="1104">Figure 3</figureCitation>
(h)). Clypeo-genal suture sulcate, almost straight. Frontoclypeal suture inconspicuous between eyes. Clypeus transversely elevated at posterior portion. Frons almost flat. Clypeal margination upturned. Ventral clypeal process produced into a small tubercle. Antennal club globose. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[744,828,351,376]" pageId="24" pageNumber="1104">Thorax</emphasis>
: pronotal disc with a shallow mid-longitudinal sulcus. Anteromedial portion of the pronotal disc with a low central knob. Transverse carina of hypomera complete, reaching the lateral edge. Anterior portion of hypomera densely coated with setae; lateral edge with a row of setae, visible in dorsal view; posterior portion with short setae near margin of procoxae. Surface of mesepimeron and mesanepisternum with green reflections; finely striate. Meso-metaventral suture straight medially. Anterior lobe of metaventrite with well-defined microgranulation. Metaventral disc flat, punctate, with a shallow longitudinal sulcus medially. Lateral lobes of metaventrite with well-defined microgranulation and shallow punctures. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1080,1150,628,653]" pageId="24" pageNumber="1104">Elytra</emphasis>
: striae thin, ill-impressed punctures throughout their length (
<figureCitation box="[860,955,663,688]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="8.[160,225,904,927]" captionTargetBox="[166,1143,144,862]" captionTargetId="figure-495@8.[163,1153,142,873]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figure 4. Details of Scatonomus morphology. (a) S. mitzae sp. nov., microgranulated interstrial surface (white arrow indicating the elytral stria); (b) S. janssensi, detail of elytral striae; (c) S. thalassinus, surface of pronotal disc (wrinkles, square); (d) S. mitzae sp. nov., puncticulate pronotal surface (white arrow, a coase puncture; black arrow, a fine puncture); (e) S. janssensi, ocellate punctures on pronotum; (f) S. fasciculatus, striate surface on mesepimeron; (g) S. janssensi, broad and transverse carina at the posterior portion of clypeus (white arrow) and longitudinal carina (black arrow); (h) holotype of S. xanthopygus (synonym of S. chalybaeus), dry body fat partially covering the pygidial disc; (i, j) Abdominal ventrites of S. thalassinus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5020911" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5020911/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="1104">Figure 4</figureCitation>
(a)). Seventh stria absent at the basal one-seventh of elytra. Eighth stria carinate, effaced along anterior half. Ninth stria finely carinate, visible at the apical portion of elytra. Tenth stria absent. Interstriae with microgranulated surface (
<figureCitation box="[630,723,767,792]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="8.[160,225,904,927]" captionTargetBox="[166,1143,144,862]" captionTargetId="figure-495@8.[163,1153,142,873]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figure 4. Details of Scatonomus morphology. (a) S. mitzae sp. nov., microgranulated interstrial surface (white arrow indicating the elytral stria); (b) S. janssensi, detail of elytral striae; (c) S. thalassinus, surface of pronotal disc (wrinkles, square); (d) S. mitzae sp. nov., puncticulate pronotal surface (white arrow, a coase puncture; black arrow, a fine puncture); (e) S. janssensi, ocellate punctures on pronotum; (f) S. fasciculatus, striate surface on mesepimeron; (g) S. janssensi, broad and transverse carina at the posterior portion of clypeus (white arrow) and longitudinal carina (black arrow); (h) holotype of S. xanthopygus (synonym of S. chalybaeus), dry body fat partially covering the pygidial disc; (i, j) Abdominal ventrites of S. thalassinus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5020911" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5020911/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="1104">Figure 4</figureCitation>
(a)). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[773,1002,767,792]" pageId="24" pageNumber="1104">Legs [ventral view]</emphasis>
: anterior half of profemora densely puncticulate; posterior half with setose punctures. Outer edge of protibia with three weakly defined teeth, shallowly emarginate between teeth. Outer edge of mesotibia and metatibia with a row of small teeth at its basal two-thirds. Outer carina of mesotibia and metatibia with a row of well-defined teeth and setae. Inner margin of metatibia carinate, except by the apical third. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[700,817,940,965]" pageId="24" pageNumber="1104">Abdomen</emphasis>
: surface of ventrites punctate; lateral portion of ventrites I–IV with well-defined microgranulation. Posterior half of ventrites II–IV with a row of shallow punctures. Ventrite V slightly shorter than VI at medial portion. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[345,459,1044,1069]" pageId="24" pageNumber="1104">Pygidium</emphasis>
: 1/3 wider than long. Surface densely puncticulate. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="1104">Genital capsule</emphasis>
: paramera apex divided into apical and lateral lobes by a deep V-shaped emargination. Apical lobe rounded; lateral lobe truncate, approximately as wide as long (
<figureCitation box="[1065,1155,1114,1139]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="9.[160,225,1191,1214]" captionTargetBox="[224,1152,142,1131]" captionTargetId="figure-205@9.[163,1153,142,1159]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figure 5. Aedeagus, detail of right paramera and endophallic sclerites. (a) Scatonomus barbatus stat. rev.; (b) S. chalybaeus; (c) S. fasciculatus; (d) S. foresti sp. nov.; (e) S. insignis; (f) S. janssensi; (g) S. mitzae sp. nov.; (h) S. thalassinus; (i) S. viridis; (j) endophallic sclerites of S. fasciculatus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5020913" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5020913/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="1104">Figure 5</figureCitation>
(g)). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[211,298,1148,1173]" pageId="24" pageNumber="1104">Female</emphasis>
: unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
